# Cursor Rules — brain-app (Eldad's Brain Dashboard)

## Language & Framework
- TypeScript strict mode (no `any`)
- React 19 with functional components only
- React Router 7 for navigation
- Lucide React for icons
- Vite for build

## Code Style
- Use `interface` (not `type`) for object shapes
- Named `interface Props {}` for every component — never inline types
- JSDoc on every exported function, component, and hook
- `#region` / `#endregion` blocks for file sections
- Max 300 lines per file
- PascalCase for component files, camelCase for utils/hooks

## Architecture
- Feature folder pattern: `src/pages/<feature>/` with orchestrator
- Orchestrator components: layout ONLY, no business logic
- Custom hooks for all state logic and data transformations
- Barrel exports (`index.ts`) in every feature folder
- No circular dependencies

## Component Pattern
```tsx
/** Brief description of component */
interface Props {
  /** prop description */
  propName: string;
}
export default function ComponentName({ propName }: Props) {
  return <div>{propName}</div>;
}
```

## Naming
- Components: `PascalCase.tsx` (e.g., `StatsBar.tsx`)
- Hooks: `use<Name>` in `hooks.ts` (e.g., `useMeetings`)
- Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` (e.g., `DAYS_HE`)
- Utils: descriptive names (e.g., `calendarUtils.ts` not `utils.ts`)

## Important Context
- App is RTL (Hebrew) — `dir="rtl"`
- All data in localStorage (no backend)
- Dark theme with glass morphism
- All pages lazy-loaded in `main.tsx`
- Date format: `YYYY-MM-DD` strings
